# Fluff Date: 2026-02-26 19:50:04
<overview>
<p>The Kyushu-class frigate was the first modern WarShip produced by the Draconis Combine, and the most numerous class in its post-Clan Invasion naval fleet. Commissioned during the mid-3050s, the Kyushu was designed primarily for the transport and defense of invasion task forces, filling a critical gap in the Combine's ability to project military power across interstellar distances. The class was built at two facilities: the Stellar Trek Enterprises yard at Dieron and the Midway WarShip Yard. Distinguished by a generous troop transport capacity and well-rounded defensive armament, the Kyushu earned a reputation as a dependable workhorse capable of operating independently or as part of a larger task force. Though classified as a frigate, the vessel proved itself in engagements well beyond its intended escort and transport role, and the class formed the backbone of the Combine's naval operations for over four decades.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>At 630,000 tons, the Kyushu mounted an arsenal primarily of conventional anti-fighter weaponry supported by a sizable array of capital weapons. The nose and aft each carried two NAC/40s, two NAC/20s, two NL35 naval lasers, and a single heavy naval PPC, while the fore and aft quarter arcs mounted paired NAC/35s with two NL35s. The broadsides added a NAC/20 and medium naval PPC alongside the standard NL35 pair. Every firing arc carried a comprehensive anti-fighter battery of ER large lasers, medium lasers, Artemis-enhanced LRM-20 racks, and five small pulse lasers for point defense. The vessel sustained three thrust points safely with a maximum of five, and a lithium-fusion battery enabled rapid successive jumps. The 879.5 tons of improved ferro-aluminum armor provided reasonable protection for a vessel of its class. The Kyushu's most remarkable feature was its transport capacity, centered on 108 combat machine cubicles sufficient for a complete regiment. These machines could reach a planet's surface via four attached DropShips, twelve specially modified cargo shuttles carrying two units each, or direct orbital insertion through drop pods if the vessel achieved low orbit. The crew of forty-six officers, one hundred and seventy-six enlisted, fifty-three gunners, and three hundred and twelve bay personnel occupied spacious double-occupancy cabins across six decks, each with dedicated mess and recreation facilities.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The DCS Dieron Star, DCS Galedon Explorer, and DCS Pride of New Samarkand were the first three Kyushu-class frigates to enter service in late 3058. The Galedon Explorer was destroyed in the Galedon system in 3068 when a Clan Snow Raven naval Star struck the world during the opening stages of the Jihad. The Pride of New Samarkand was presumed lost during Operation BULLDOG against Clan Smoke Jaguar in 3059. The DCS Dream of Kessel completed trials at Dieron but was similarly presumed destroyed during BULLDOG. The DCS Luthien, which underwent trials in the Togura system, was destroyed in November 3072 at Benjamin alongside two Inazuma corvettes during an unsuccessful attempt to break a Word of Blake blockade. The DCS Victory at Wolcott participated in a costly engagement at Thule in November 3062 before being destroyed during the liberation of Terra in 3079 as part of Operation SCOUR. The DCS Haruna joined Task Force Serpent, capturing the Ghost Bear JumpShip Winter Wind at the Battle of Trafalgar in December 3059 and surviving engagements above Huntress in March 3060; its ultimate fate is unrecorded. The DCS Dieron Star survived the Jihad before being destroyed at the Battle of Rasalhague on April 29, 3100. The DCS Draconis Rift, the last survivor, dealt the killing blow to the Nightlord-class battleship Ursa Major at that same battle and remained operational into the ilClan era.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Kyushu program marked the Draconis Combine's first serious effort to rebuild naval capability following the devastating losses of the Succession Wars. The design drew heavily on a pair of Federated Suns Robinson-class transports captured during the early Succession Wars, which provided baseline specifications for a vessel optimized for troop transport and invasion support rather than dedicated anti-ship combat. Construction of the new Terada assembly facility at Dieron began in August 3053, with the prototype's keel laid that same year. Components were sourced from manufacturing plants throughout the Combine, reflecting the enormous industrial commitment required to sustain a modern WarShip program. Despite this complexity, the program proceeded on schedule and the first hulls were completed by late 3057. The Midway WarShip Yard also contributed to the production run, and together the two yards made the Kyushu the most numerous modern WarShip class in Combine service.</p><p>Eight vessels were ultimately commissioned. The first three entered active service by late 3058, with four more completing shakedown trials around the same time and at least one additional hull joining Task Force Serpent's expedition into Clan space in 3059. The class was committed to nearly every major Combine naval operation from the late Clan Invasion onward, including Operation BULLDOG and the First Combine-Dominion War. Two frigates were presumed lost during BULLDOG, the class's first significant combat losses. Despite the Kyushu's origins as a transport platform, the vessels proved more than capable of defending themselves when pressed into direct engagements, and the class quickly became the primary means by which the Combine projected ground forces across interstellar distances.</p><p>The Jihad inflicted severe attrition on the class. Clan raider strikes claimed vessels in the opening stages of the conflict, while Word of Blake naval actions and blockade operations destroyed others as the war intensified. The liberation of Terra during Operation SCOUR cost the Combine another frigate. The survivors proved their endurance through decades of continued service, operating through the post-Jihad reconstruction and into the Second Combine-Dominion War. The class saw its final major fleet action at the Battle of Rasalhague in April 3100, where Combine frigates fought alongside the broader fleet. By the ilClan era, only a single Kyushu remained in Combine service, the sole survivor of a class that had served the Combine faithfully for over four decades.</p>
</history>

